<h1>Problem 839 - 2021 MODSMO, P7 of 7, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Consider a triangle \(ABC\) with incircle \(\omega\). Let \(S\) be the point on \(\omega\) such that the circumcircle of \(BSC\) is tangent to \(\omega\) and let the \(A\)-excircle be tangent to \(BC\) at \(A_1\). Prove that the tangent from \(S\) to \(\omega\) and the tangent from \(A_1\) to \(\omega\) (distinct from \(BC\)) meet on the line parallel to \(BC\) and passing through \(A\).</p>
